commit.message: Added release date
Added changelog entry for #444

Skip AnyStr tests on Python 3.13+

This is to avoid future deprecation warnings.

Fixed deprecation warning about `@no_type_check_decorator` on Python 3.13

Fixes #414.

Updated the typing_extensions dependency

Fixes #444. Closes #445.
Updated GitHub actions
Added release date

Fixed pytest plugin tests

They were messing with the global configuration, and the command line options test didn't have the proper input either.

Added support for specifying options for the pytest plugin via pytest config files

Closes #440.

Fixed mapping checks against Django's MultiValueDict

Fixes #419.
Updated ruff configuration

Fixed detection of optional TypedDict fields when NotRequired is a forward reference

Fixes #424.

Fixed generic aliases not passing checks against `type` (#433)

Co-authored-by: Alex Grönholm <alex.gronholm@nextday.fi>

commit.message:
Avoid creating ref cycles (#408)

By storing previously raised exceptions inside a local, this code created ref cycles that kept all locals in all calling stack frames alive.

This is because exceptions hold references to their tracebacks, which hold references to the relevant frames, which holds a reference to the local errors dict that holds references to the exceptions. See https://peps.python.org/pep-0344/#open-issue-garbage-collection and https://peps.python.org/pep-3110/#rationale

This breaks the cycle by deleting the local when we raise, so frames are destroyed by the normal reference counting mechanism.

This fixes some resource exhaustion issues I encountered at work.
